item.title: F**king demented: Trump's son slams Rachel Vindman for 'no ears were harmed' joke. She deletes it
item.description: ​ "No ears were harmed. Carry one with your Sunday afternoon," Vindman posted referring to the ear injury that Trump sustained when Thomas Matthew Crooks opened fire at him at a Pennsylvania rally in July. ​Donald Trump Jr called her 'f**king demented' for the statement. "Today she celebrated the assassination attempt of president Trump by a pro Ukraine mercenary," Donald Trump's aide Laura Loomer wrote on X.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Second assassination attempt on Trump triggers outrage, suspicion on all sides
item.description: US authorities prevented an assassination attempt on former President Donald Trump at a Florida resort. The suspect, Ryan Wesley Routh, was arrested after being spotted with a rifle. Trump confirmed his safety and thanked law enforcement. This incident raises concerns about security measures following two attempts in 60 days.
item.dc:creator: Chidanand Rajghatta

item.title: MAGA vs Dems: Firestorm erupts over political allegiance of Ryan Routh, suspect in Trump assassination bid
item.description: Following an alleged assassination attempt on Donald Trump by Ryan Routh, Republicans and Democrats disputed his political affiliation. Both parties referenced his voting record and donations to bolster their arguments. The event triggered social media confrontations, fund-raising campaigns, and controversy surrounding a tweet from Elon Musk.
item.dc:creator: Chidanand Rajghatta

item.title: Time Magazine cover viral as it 'predicted' 2nd assassination attempt on Donald Trump
item.description: Social media users pointed out how the Time Magazine cover eerily predicted the exact situation in which the second assassination attempt on Donald Trump took place. Captioned 'In trouble', the cover depicted Donald Trump stuck at golf course's sand trap. While the article was about how Kamala Harris knocked Donald Trump off course, the cover photo became ominously prophetic.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Meghan, Harry 'concerned' over 'dictator' report. They probably know who did it
item.description: Who could have pushed such an article is also no mystery to them as a number of staff members quit Harry, Meghan's team recently. "There are fears that there could be a disgruntled former member of staff who is putting out mistruths which are designed to make them look bad," the source said.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 30 killed in tribal clashes near gold mine in Papua New Guinea, security forces granted 'emergency powers'
item.description: Clashes between rival tribes over a disputed gold mine in Papua New Guinea have left at least 30 dead. Police have been given emergency powers, including lethal force authorisation, to restore order. The Porgera gold mine has halted operations due to the violence, and measures like an alcohol ban and curfew are being enforced.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Did Lester Holt say Trump deserved to be shot at? Here's the whole truth
item.description: MSNBC's Lester Holt has been criticized for seemingly suggesting that Donald Trump deserved a recent assassination attempt. Holt connected the incident to baseless claims made by Trump and JD Vance about Haitian immigrants in Springfield, Ohio. These unfounded allegations have led to bomb threats against Haitians, despite originating from unverified sources.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Ex-BBC anchor Huw Edwards avoids jail over indecent photos of children
item.description: Former BBC anchor Huw Edwards avoided jail time after pleading guilty to possessing indecent images of children. He was sentenced to a six-month prison term, suspended for two years, and must register as a sex offender for seven years. Edwards resigned from the BBC in April following his arrest.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Trump said he was disappointed he could not finish his game'
item.description: Donald Trump survived a second assassination attempt during a golf game in Florida. Despite the ordeal, he humorously regretted not finishing his round. Secret Service agents identified and engaged the attacker, who fled but was later apprehended by police. Trump remained unharmed and was escorted to Mar-a-Lago. "I was even and I had a birdie putt," Donald Trump said to his friends and aides lamenting that he had been set to shoot under par.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Trajectory is clear': Israeli defense minister signals declining hope for peaceful resolution with Hezbollah
item.description: Israeli defense minister Yoav Gallant informed US defense secretary Lloyd Austin that the chances for a peaceful resolution with Hezbollah are dwindling. With Hezbollah's continued alliance with Hamas, Israel aims to dismantle Hamas and ensure hostages' return. The ongoing conflict has caused significant casualties in Gaza.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: US govt knew about Ryan Routh and they...: Laura Loomer's theory on 2nd attempt to 'kill' Donald Trump
item.description: Laura Loomer said Ryan Routh served in the US foreign legion in Ukraine which is reportedly tied to the CIA. She said New York Times and NewsWeek interviewed him and published his profile. "So the US government knew this guy was doing illegal mercenary work and they never stopped him. Even worse, the anti-Trump Leftist media wrote glowing profiles about him and gave him a platform."
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Severe flooding ravages central Europe, claims at least 10 lives
item.description: Severe flooding has devastated central Europe, leading to at least 10 fatalities from Poland to Romania. Intense rainfall has caused towns to be submerged or damaged. The Czech-Polish border areas and eastern Romania are heavily impacted. Governments are declaring states of disaster and evacuating residents as rising rivers threaten larger cities.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Andrew O'Keefe arrested for breaching bail conditions after drug overdose
item.description: Andrew O'Keefe, former Australian TV host, was arrested for violating bail conditions following a drug overdose. Paramedics revived him before taking him to the hospital. O'Keefe recently lost an appeal against domestic violence convictions and had previously been found guilty of assault and breaching an apprehended violence order earlier this year.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Spike in calls to poison control centers due to kids consuming energy drinks
item.description: US poison centers report a concerning 20% rise in calls about children consuming energy drinks in 2023, with total calls increasing to 2,834 from last year's 2,323. High caffeine content poses serious health risks for children. Both the FDA and American Academy of Pediatrics advise against consumption by children and teenagers.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Harvest moon lunar eclipse: When and how to watch?
item.description: On Tuesday evening, skywatchers in the United States, Europe, Africa, western Asia, and parts of Antarctica can observe a partial lunar eclipse coinciding with a super full Moon. Known as the Harvest Moon due to its proximity to the autumnal equinox, this event will also result in King Tides. The eclipse peaks at 10:44 pm EDT.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Who is Gisele Pelicot? Drugged and raped for a decade, woman becomes symbol of courage and resilience
item.description: In France, hundreds have shown support for Gisèle Pélicot, who accused her ex-husband of drugging and facilitating her rape by strangers over ten years. The ongoing trial involves 50 men and has garnered significant attention, highlighting issues of sexual violence and consent. Pélicot's bravery has been widely praised. She has made her court case public so that people can be alerted.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Over 50% Americans feel Harris is the winner of presidential debate against Trump: New poll
item.description: According to an ABC/Ipsos poll, most Americans believe Vice President Kamala Harris won last week's presidential debate against former President Donald Trump. The survey shows 58 percent of respondents favored Harris, while only 36 percent chose Trump. The debate improved Harris's favorability ratings but had a negative impact on Trump's.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Philippines says 'we have not lost' South China Sea reef after pullout
item.description: The Philippines withdrew a coast guard ship from Sabina Shoal in the South China Sea citing damage and supply issues but insists it hasn't abandoned the area. Despite China's aggressive actions and sovereignty claims, Manila asserts the shoal remains part of its exclusive economic zone and plans continued presence.

item.title: Donald Trump assassination attempt: What was Ryan Wesley Routh planning to do with GoPro camera?
item.description: Ryan Wesely Routh was arrested after an apparent assassination attempt on former President Donald Trump at his West Palm Beach golf course. The suspect, who had criticized Trump on social media and supported Ukraine, was found with a rifle and filming equipment. Authorities tracked him down with the help of a witness.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
